      "prompt_text": "You are taking the ArchitectureIQ benchmark.\n\nEach question describes a synthetic dataset and several candidate training setups (model, optimizer, loss). All choices train on the same data with the same sample budget. Your task is to identify which setup will achieve the **best test MSE** on the held-out test set after the fixed training budget — using architecture and learning-mechanics reasoning only (no training results are provided).\n\n## Dataset\n**Family:** univariate regression on `[0, 1]`.\n\n- Input and target are 1-D scalars.\n- Training and test points are sampled uniformly on the domain.\n- Labels are noiseless; the target is a symbolic expression of `x`.\n\n### Synthesis (PyTorch)\n```python\ndef target(x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n    return (torch.tensor(0.5, dtype=x.dtype, device=x.device) + torch.tanh(2 * ((torch.tensor(0.5, dtype=x.dtype, device=x.device) - x))))\n\n\ndef synthesize(\n    *,\n    train_size: int = 256,\n    test_size: int = 256,\n    point_seed: int = 1000,\n    domain_low: float = 0.0,\n    domain_high: float = 1.0,\n) -> tuple[torch.Tensor, torch.Tensor, torch.Tensor, torch.Tensor]:\n    gen = torch.Generator().manual_seed(point_seed)\n    train_x = torch.rand(train_size, generator=gen) * (domain_high - domain_low) + domain_low\n    test_x = torch.rand(test_size, generator=gen) * (domain_high - domain_low) + domain_low\n    train_y = target(train_x)\n    test_y = target(test_x)\n    return train_x.unsqueeze(-1), train_y.unsqueeze(-1), test_x.unsqueeze(-1), test_y.unsqueeze(-1)\n```\n\n### Data splits and training protocol\n- Target expression (canonical): `0.5 + tanh(2*(0.5 - x))`\n- Train split size: 256 fixed `(x, y)` pairs\n- Test split size: 256 fixed `(x, y)` pairs (held out)\n- Input domain: [0.0, 1.0], uniform sampling\n- Point-sampling seed: 1000 (materializes the fixed train/test splits)\n- Minibatch construction: each step draws `batch_size` train indices uniformly at random **with replacement**\n- Evaluation: **test MSE** is mean squared error on the entire fixed test split\n- Randomness: `torch.manual_seed(seed)` once before model init and the training loop\n- Reference device: CPU\n\n## Sample budget (same for all choices)\n- training_steps: 4\n- batch_size: 32\n- total_samples_seen: 128 (= training_steps × batch_size)\n\n## Evaluation metric\n- Ground-truth ranking uses **test_mse** on the held-out test split.\n- Each choice is trained independently for **10** seeds (`0`..`9`), one `torch.manual_seed(seed)` per run.\n- The correct choice has the lowest **mean** test_mse across seeds.\n\n## Choices\n\n### Choice A\n\n**Model (natural language)**\n- Type: MLP\n- Depth: 2 hidden layers\n- Width: 256 (all hidden layers)\n- Residual connections: False\n- Layer norm per layer: [False, True]\n- Activations: [leaky_relu, leaky_relu]\n- Initialization: PyTorch Linear defaults\n\n**Model code**\n```python\ndef _activation(name: str) -> nn.Module:\n    mapping = {\n        \"relu\": nn.ReLU(),\n        \"leaky_relu\": nn.LeakyReLU(0.1),\n        \"gelu\": nn.GELU(),\n        \"silu\": nn.SiLU(),\n    }\n    return mapping[name]\n\n\nclass MLPBlock(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, width: int, activation: str, use_layer_norm: bool, use_residual: bool) -> None:\n        super().__init__()\n        self.use_residual = use_residual\n        self.norm = nn.LayerNorm(width) if use_layer_norm else None\n        self.linear = nn.Linear(width, width)\n        self.act = _activation(activation)\n\n    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n        h = x\n        if self.norm is not None:\n            h = self.norm(h)\n        h = self.linear(h)\n        h = self.act(h)\n        if self.use_residual:\n            h = h + x\n        return h\n\n\nclass Model(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self) -> None:\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(1, 256),\n        MLPBlock(width=256, activation='leaky_relu', use_layer_norm=False, use_residual=False),\n        MLPBlock(width=256, activation='leaky_relu', use_layer_norm=True, use_residual=False),\n            nn.Linear(256, 1),\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n        return self.net(x)\n```\n\n**Optimizer**\n- Optimizer: RMSprop\n- Learning rate: 0.0001\n- Weight decay: 0.0001\n\n```python\ndef build_optimizer(model: nn.Module) -> torch.optim.Optimizer:\n    params = model.parameters()\n    return torch.optim.RMSprop(params, lr=0.0001, weight_decay=0.0001)\n```\n\n**Loss**\n- Loss: MSE on the minibatch + L1 weight penalty (lambda=0.001, mean absolute parameter magnitude)\n\n```python\ndef loss_fn(model: nn.Module, pred: torch.Tensor, target: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n    base = torch.mean((pred - target) ** 2)\n    l1 = torch.mean(torch.stack([torch.mean(torch.abs(p)) for p in model.parameters()]))\n    return base + 0.001 * l1\n```\n\n### Choice B\n\n**Model (natural language)**\n- Type: MLP\n- Depth: 3 hidden layers\n- Width: 16 (all hidden layers)\n- Residual connections: False\n- Layer norm per layer: [False, False, False]\n- Activations: [gelu, silu, relu]\n- Initialization: PyTorch Linear defaults\n\n**Model code**\n```python\ndef _activation(name: str) -> nn.Module:\n    mapping = {\n        \"relu\": nn.ReLU(),\n        \"leaky_relu\": nn.LeakyReLU(0.1),\n        \"gelu\": nn.GELU(),\n        \"silu\": nn.SiLU(),\n    }\n    return mapping[name]\n\n\nclass MLPBlock(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, width: int, activation: str, use_layer_norm: bool, use_residual: bool) -> None:\n        super().__init__()\n        self.use_residual = use_residual\n        self.norm = nn.LayerNorm(width) if use_layer_norm else None\n        self.linear = nn.Linear(width, width)\n        self.act = _activation(activation)\n\n    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n        h = x\n        if self.norm is not None:\n            h = self.norm(h)\n        h = self.linear(h)\n        h = self.act(h)\n        if self.use_residual:\n            h = h + x\n        return h\n\n\nclass Model(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self) -> None:\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(1, 16),\n        MLPBlock(width=16, activation='gelu', use_layer_norm=False, use_residual=False),\n        MLPBlock(width=16, activation='silu', use_layer_norm=False, use_residual=False),\n        MLPBlock(width=16, activation='relu', use_layer_norm=False, use_residual=False),\n            nn.Linear(16, 1),\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n        return self.net(x)\n```\n\n**Optimizer**\n- Optimizer: RMSprop\n- Learning rate: 0.0001\n- Weight decay: 0.0001\n\n```python\ndef build_optimizer(model: nn.Module) -> torch.optim.Optimizer:\n    params = model.parameters()\n    return torch.optim.RMSprop(params, lr=0.0001, weight_decay=0.0001)\n```\n\n**Loss**\n- Loss: MSE on the minibatch + L1 weight penalty (lambda=0.001, mean absolute parameter magnitude)\n\n```python\ndef loss_fn(model: nn.Module, pred: torch.Tensor, target: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n    base = torch.mean((pred - target) ** 2)\n    l1 = torch.mean(torch.stack([torch.mean(torch.abs(p)) for p in model.parameters()]))\n    return base + 0.001 * l1\n```\n\n## Your answer\nReply with a single letter (A, B).",
